Ticket ID: MOB-AUTO-2026-02-IP16PM-PROFILES
Title: iPhone 16 Pro Max — Live Profile Automation Framework (Battery / Performance / Visual)
Classification: Mobile Automation / Profile Management
Date: 16 February 2026 – Present
System: iPhone 16 Pro Max
OS: iOS 18+
Status: Active / Fully Operational

System Identification
	• Device: iPhone 16 Pro Max
	• Manufacturer: Apple Inc.
	• Purpose: Fully automated profile switching framework for Battery, Performance, and Visual Experience modes
	• Usage: Personal and productivity device, manual and automated optimization

Executive Summary
This ticket defines a fully automated live profile switching system for the iPhone 16 Pro Max. It dynamically manages three predefined profiles:
Profile	Purpose
Battery Mode	Maximum efficiency and battery longevity
Performance Mode	Maximum responsiveness and performance during charging
Visual Experience Mode	Maximum visual quality and UI fidelity
Business Impact:
	• Manual switching previously required constant intervention
	• Low battery inefficiencies and unstructured visual-performance management
	• Automatic performance boosts were unavailable during charging
Post-Implementation Benefits:
	• Fully autonomous battery protection
	• Automatic performance activation when charger is connected
	• Instant manual access to Visual Mode
	• Manual override available via unified selector
	• Zero maintenance required
	• Enterprise-grade operational reliability
Root Cause: iOS does not provide native profile systems. Native automation and Shortcuts allow creation of a virtual profile controller. Certain visual settings require one-time manual configuration due to Apple limitations.

1. Architecture Overview
System Components:
	• 3 Shortcuts → Profile executors
	• 2 Automations → Automatic triggers
	• Manual Visual Mode trigger shortcut
	• Manual-only visual configuration layer

2. Shortcuts (Profile Executors)
2.1 Activate Battery Mode
	• Low Power Mode → ON
	• Brightness → 30%
	• Appearance → Dark
	• Auto-Lock → 30 sec
	• Focus → Do Not Disturb ON
	• Reduce Motion → ON
	• Reduce White Point → ON, 25%
2.2 Activate Performance Mode
	• Low Power Mode → OFF
	• Brightness → 60%
	• Appearance → Dark
	• Auto-Lock → 2 min
	• Focus → Do Not Disturb OFF
	• Reduce Motion → OFF
	• Reduce White Point → OFF
2.3 Activate Visual Experience Mode
	• Low Power Mode → OFF
	• Brightness → 80%
	• Appearance → Dark (or Light)
	• Auto-Lock → 5 min
	• Focus → OFF
	• Reduce Motion → OFF
	• Reduce White Point → OFF
	• Manual Access: Add to Home Screen for one-tap activation

3. Automations (Automatic Triggers)
3.1 Battery Protection Trigger
	• Trigger: Battery Level < 30%
	• Action: Run Shortcut → Activate Battery Mode
	• Settings: Ask Before Running OFF, Notify When Run OFF
3.2 Performance Mode Trigger
	• Trigger: Charger Connected
	• Action: Conditional Shortcut:
		○ IF Battery ≥ 20% → Activate Performance Mode
		○ ELSE → Activate Battery Mode
	• Settings: Ask Before Running OFF, Notify When Run OFF
Logic Summary:
	• Battery < 30% → Battery Mode auto activates
	• Charger connected AND battery ≥ 20% → Performance Mode activates
	• Charger connected AND battery < 20% → Battery Mode remains active
	• Visual Mode → Manual activation

4. Manual Settings Required (Apple Limitation Layer)
One-time configuration:
	• Accessibility → Display & Text Size: Increase Contrast OFF, Smart Invert OFF, Classic Invert OFF, Reduce Transparency OFF
	• Accessibility → Motion: Auto-Play Message Effects ON, Auto-Play Animated Images ON
	• Display & Brightness: True Tone ON, Night Shift OFF (optional)
	• Accessibility → Touch: Haptic Touch → Fast

5. Manual Profile Selector Extension
	• Shortcut Name: Profile Selector
	• Actions:
		○ Menu Action → Options: Battery Mode, Performance Mode, Visual Experience Mode
		○ Each menu item linked to its corresponding shortcut
	• Home Screen Placement: “Profiles” → centralized manual override
	• Behavior: Instant profile switching <1 second, overrides automation without conflict

6. Optional Visual Mode Enhancements (Manual Only)
	• High-quality OLED-optimized wallpaper
	• Per-app performance settings verified
	• Manual-only visual polish and depth effects

7. Validation Procedure
	• Test Case 1: Battery Mode → Enable Low Power Mode manually → Confirm brightness, motion, focus
	• Test Case 2: Performance Mode → Connect charger → Confirm Low Power Mode disables automatically
	• Test Case 3: Visual Mode → Tap Visual Mode shortcut → Confirm brightness increase, motion fully enabled
	• Test Case 4: Profile Selector → Select any profile → Confirm instant activation
Results:
	• Fully automatic battery protection
	• Fully automatic performance activation when charging
	• Instant manual Visual Mode
	• Manual selector allows full profile override
	• Zero reboot required
	• Zero maintenance required
	• System stability: Enterprise-grade
	• Automation reliability: Maximum

Operational Characteristics
	• Fully automatic profile switching
	• Instant manual override via selector
	• Conditional safety logic for battery protection
	• Manual and automatic control coexist without conflict
System Status: Complete, fully operational
Automation Level: Maximum achievable within iOS constraints
